<!--Shidori Shrine (Nirasaki)-->, [[Nara Prefecture]])
* ''Shidori Shrine (倭文神社)'' in ''Shidori-go, Kume District, Mimasaka Province'' – {{ill|Shidori Shrine (Tsuyama)|en}}
<!--Shidori Shrine (Nirasaki)--> (Yukikita, {{ill|Tsuyama, Okayama|en}}
<!--Shidori Shrine (Nirasaki)-->, [[Okayama Prefecture]])
* ''Shidori Shrine (倭文神社)'' in ''Shidori-go, Mihara District, Awaji Province'' – {{ill|Shidori Shrine (Awaji)|en}}
<!--Shidori Shrine (Nirasaki)--> (Shidori, {{ill|Minamiawaji, Hyogo|en}}
<!--Shidori Shrine (Nirasaki)-->, [[Hyogo Prefecture]])

Additionally, ''{{ill|Ōmika Shrine|8=ja|9=大甕神社|en}}
<!--Shidori Shrine (Nirasaki)-->'' ({{ill|Hitachi, Ibaraki|en}}
<!--Shidori Shrine (Nirasaki)-->, [[Ibaraki Prefecture]]) also enshrines ''Takahatsuchi-no-Mikoto|ja|天羽槌雄神|1=Takehazuchi|fr|Takehazuchi|zh|天羽槌雄神|lt=Takehazuchi-no-Mikoto''. Similarly, ''{{ill|Ishii Shrine|en}}
<!--Shidori Shrine (Nirasaki)-->'' ({{ill|Kasama, Ibaraki|en}}
<!--Shidori Shrine (Nirasaki)-->, [[Ibaraki Prefecture]]) enshrines the same deity, with a large sacred rock called "Mitarai" located to the south.
== See Also ==

* ''{{ill|Takahatsuchi-no-Mikoto|ja|天羽槌雄神|1=Takehazuchi|fr|Takehazuchi|zh|天羽槌雄神|lt=Takehazuchi-no-Mikoto|en}}
